# Key Patterns & Pitfalls

## React Strict Mode (Development)
Next.js dev mode double-mounts effects. Any `useEffect` managing a persistent connection (WebSocket, LiveKit Room) MUST use locally-scoped variables for cancellation/state rather than `useRef`, so each mount/unmount cycle is independent. See `useLivekitRoom.js` for the canonical pattern.

## LiveKit Identity
Each browser tab needs a unique LiveKit identity. Format: `{supabaseUserId}-{tabSessionId}`. The real user ID is stored in `participant.metadata` as JSON. Always extract userId from metadata, never parse identity strings.

## Track Lifecycle
- `unpublishTrack()` must use `stopOnUnpublish: false` to keep the underlying MediaStreamTrack alive for potential re-publishing.
- `BroadcastStreamControls` resets `isStreaming` state via a `useEffect` watching for `room === null`, ensuring UI stays consistent through disconnects.
- On mount (or HMR), `StreamControls` syncs `isStreaming` with `room.localParticipant.trackPublications` — if broadcast tracks are already published, the UI reflects that rather than resetting to "stopped". Uses `parseBroadcastTrackName()` exported from `RealtimeContext.js`.

## Socket.IO Scoping
All relay messages are scoped to `stageId` rooms. There is no global broadcast fallback. The server silently discards messages with no stageId.

## Browser Tab / Window Visibility
Video elements stop playing when tabs are backgrounded or windows are occluded. `VideoObject.js` listens for both `visibilitychange` and `window focus` events and re-attaches `srcObject` + calls `.play()` when focus is regained. Stream thumbnails (`Stage/index.js`) use the same pattern with direct `<video>` elements instead of canvas snapshots.

## Audio for Professional Sources
All browser audio processing is force-disabled: `echoCancellation`, `noiseSuppression`, `autoGainControl` all set to `false`. This is intentional for use with audio interfaces (Scarlett, etc.) and should not be "fixed".

## Supabase Auth Refresh
Supabase refreshes tokens on `visibilitychange`, triggering `onAuthStateChange`. The `useUser.js` `fetchUserRole` effect depends on `[user?.id]` (not `[user]`) to avoid redundant DB queries on every token refresh.

## Environment Variables
- `LIVEKIT_API_KEY`, `LIVEKIT_API_SECRET`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_LIVEKIT_SERVER_URL` — LiveKit config
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_KEY`, `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` — Supabase config
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_REALTIME_SERVER_ADDRESS`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_REALTIME_SERVER_PORT` — Socket.IO server URL/port
- See `example.env` and `example.dev.env` for defaults
